title: Bug 49235: ServletContainerInitializer onStartup(Set<Class<? classSet is not expected class
description: The ServletContainerInitializer onStartup method is not returning the expected output. Currently, it outputs 'MySomeClass' but I expect it to output 'MySomeClass'. This issue is not yet implemented in the Servlet 3.0 specification. My code works fine on Glassfish 3.0.
EB: The current value of classSet is not the expected class.
SR: 1. Update the code to use the expected class for classSet. 2. Run the program and observe the output. The expected output should now be 'MySomeClass'.
